# CODEOWNERS — auto-requests review from the listed owner on matching paths.
#
# IMPORTANT: This file only *requests* reviewers. It does NOT block pushes or
# merges on its own. To actually require these reviews before merging to `main`,
# enable a branch protection rule (or ruleset) on `main` with:
#   - Require a pull request before merging
#   - Require review from Code Owners
#   - (recommended) Restrict who can push to matching branches
#
# Owner is the primary maintainer. To scale to multiple maintainers later,
# create an org team with write access (e.g. @tarkovtracker-org/maintainers)
# and replace @DysektAI below. Owners must have write access or the rule is ignored.
#
# No catch-all (`*`) rule on purpose: most routine PRs stay ungated. Only the
# critical paths below request review.
#
# DEPENDABOT INTERACTION: some owned paths (/.github/, /workers/, /package.json,
# /package-lock.json) overlap with the Dependabot auto-merge allowlist in
# .github/workflows/dependabot-auto-merge.yml. CODEOWNERS cannot exclude a bot
# author, so if you enable "Require review from Code Owners" on `main`, those
# Dependabot PRs will block on a code-owner approval that no workflow provides
# and auto-merge will stall. Before enabling that rule, either exclude Dependabot
# from it (e.g. a ruleset bypass actor) or add a code-owner auto-approval step to
# the auto-merge workflow.

# CI/CD, automation, and repo governance (incl. this file)
/.github/                 @DysektAI

# Database schema migrations (data-loss risk)
/supabase/migrations/     @DysektAI

# Edge functions: auth, billing webhook, account deletion
/supabase/functions/      @DysektAI

# Public API gateway: auth + rate limiting
/workers/                 @DysektAI

# Server routes, API-protection middleware, and route guards
/app/server/              @DysektAI
/app/middleware/          @DysektAI

# Build, runtime, security, and release configuration
/nuxt.config.ts           @DysektAI
/wrangler.toml            @DysektAI
/package.json             @DysektAI
/package-lock.json        @DysektAI
/eslint.config.mjs        @DysektAI
/tsconfig.json            @DysektAI
/commitlint.config.js     @DysektAI
/.releaserc.json          @DysektAI

# Agent contract + source locale (drift / instruction integrity)
/AGENTS.md                @DysektAI
/app/locales/en.json      @DysektAI
